Felt good but my double cork needs work. I learned how to double from tumbling first with a backwards takeoff so I tend to arch in my twist bc I pull my twist slightly too early. My swing leg also impulsively locks out when it’s time to spin which makes it drop instead of finishing the swing to help the twist and the flip. That’s what I need to fix to hit a TRUE dub dub (dub cork swing dub cork) Don’t even mention my spotting, I don’t see the floor until the end, and I know I’m supposed to spot the floor in every twist. I gotta get back to basics. I’ve only done dub full swing dub cork 7 times. I need to train on tramp but I’m one of those that can’t stand tramp. I didn’t grow up on one so it’s still so foreign at 30, but I know it holds the secrets. Sorry for the rant. I know what I need to do. If you have any other advice let me know. 

📹 @scottbrowdernow
